cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with networked control systems, which are typically studied in the subfield of control systems (cs.SY). The use of machine learning for dynamics modeling suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed method to robotics (cs.RO) is also possible, given the importance of efficient control in robotics. Finally, the use of event-triggered control and the focus on reducing the number of samples suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
